OL,3,CReform UK's ex-mayoral candidate set
OL,4,Cto become Walsall Council leader
OL,6,FElaine Williams, Reform UK's 2024 West
OL,7,FMidlands mayoral candidate, is set to
OL,8,Fbecome leader of Walsall Council after
OL,9,Fbeing elected group leader at a
OL,10,Fmeeting of the party's councillors on
OL,11,FSaturday.
OL,13,FWilliams, who finished fourth in the
OL,14,F2024 mayoral race with 5.8% of the
OL,15,Fvote, is now in line to take charge
OL,16,Ffollowing Reform UK's surge in
OL,17,FWalsall, where the party won 40 of the
OL,18,F60 seats at the May 7 local elections.
OL,20,FShe represents the Short Heath ward in
OL,21,Fthe borough.
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G1/6
OL,2,W+.! +,*%/"-'"-$/*%/*%/.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
